            <div class="card-body">
                <div class="panel-group1" id="accordion1">
                    <div class="panel panel-default mb-1">
                        <div class="panel-heading1 ">
                            <h4 class="panel-title1">
                                <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFour" aria-expanded="false">Code of Conduct</a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseFour" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-expanded="false" style="">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                <p>
                                A code of conduct lays out an organization's expectations and guiding principles for appropriate workplace behaviour. As illustrated by the samples, some policies also provide legal and ethical guidelines for 
                                relationships between employees, service users and clients. A code of conduct policy should: Be designed with consideration for your organization's values, the clients you work with and the service you provide 
                                Be driven by the fact that your organization's reputation and work environment are based on the actions and behaviours of your employees Provide guidelines for acceptable behaviour Emphasize use of good judgment 
                                Require compliance with all applicable legislation Provide examples of prohibited actions or behaviour that are regarded as misconduct (and it may specify the consequences of violations), but state that these 
                                are examples only and not all inclusive Refer to other related policies (for example: handling of confidential information, harassment, and conflict of interest) The samples below show a variety of ways to address 
                                code of conduct in a policy. Your code of conduct should be designed to suit the needs and expectations in your unique environment. After that, awareness and implementation become 
                                the keys to the success of a useful and practical code of conduct.    
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel panel-default mb-1">
                        <div class="panel-heading1">
                            <h4 class="panel-title1">
                                <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFive" aria-expanded="false">Drug and Alcohol Policy</a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseFive" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-expanded="false" style="">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                            <p>
                              <strong>1. Purpose</strong> Technified Labs is committed to providing a safe, healthy, and productive work environment for all employees. This Drug and Alcohol Policy outlines the company's expectations and guidelines regarding the use of drugs and alcohol in the workplace to ensure the safety of our employees, clients, and visitors, and to maintain the company's reputation and performance standards.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                              <strong>2. Scope</strong> This policy applies to all employees, contractors, temporary workers, and visitors of Technified Labs while they are on company premises, engaged in company-related activities, or representing the company in any capacity.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                              <strong>3. Prohibited Substance Use</strong> The use, possession, sale, distribution, or being under the influence of illegal drugs, unauthorized prescription drugs, or any substance that impairs judgment, coordination, or alertness is strictly prohibited during working hours, on company premises, or while representing the company.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                              <strong>4. Alcohol Use</strong> 4.1. Responsible Alcohol Consumption: Technified Labs recognizes that moderate alcohol consumption may be acceptable in certain social and professional settings. However, employees are expected to exercise responsible alcohol consumption and never allow it to impair their ability to perform their duties or to contribute to an unsafe work environment.
                            </p>
                            <p>4.2. Alcohol in the Workplace: The consumption of alcohol during working hours, on company premises, or while operating company equipment is strictly prohibited, unless explicitly authorized by management for special events or occasions.</p>
                            <p>
                              <strong>5. Prescription Medications</strong> Employees who are taking prescription medications that may affect their ability to perform their job safely or effectively are required to inform their supervisor or HR department. This information will be kept confidential and used only to determine whether any temporary workplace adjustments are necessary.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                              <strong>6. Impairment and Reporting</strong> 6.1. Employees who believe that a colleague may be impaired due to drug or alcohol use must immediately report their concerns to their supervisor, manager, or HR department.
                            </p>
                            <p>6.2. Managers and supervisors who suspect an employee's impairment have the responsibility to address the situation promptly and confidentially. This may involve temporarily removing the employee from their duties and assessing their fitness for work.</p>
                            <p>
                              <strong>7. Testing and Consequences</strong> 7.1. Drug and Alcohol Testing: Technified Labs reserves the right to conduct drug and alcohol testing in circumstances where there is reasonable suspicion of substance abuse, after workplace accidents, or as required by law.
                            </p>
                            <p>7.2. Consequences: Violation of this policy may result in disciplinary actions, up to and including termination of employment, in accordance with the company's progressive discipline process.</p>
                            <p>
                              <strong>8. Support and Assistance</strong> Technified Labs is committed to supporting employees who may be struggling with substance abuse issues. Employees are encouraged to seek help through the company's Employee Assistance Program (EAP) or appropriate external resources. The company will provide guidance and assistance in finding appropriate treatment and support.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                              <strong>9. Compliance</strong> All employees are required to read, understand, and comply with this Drug and Alcohol Policy. Non-compliance may result in disciplinary action, up to and including termination.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                              <strong>10. Policy Review</strong> This policy will be reviewed periodically to ensure its effectiveness and relevance. Any necessary updates will be communicated to all employees.
                            </p>
                            <p>By adhering to this Drug and Alcohol Policy, we can maintain a safe, healthy, and productive work environment for all at Technified Labs.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel panel-default mb-1">
                        <div class="panel-heading1">
                            <h4 class="panel-title1">
                                <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseSix" aria-expanded="false">Probation Policy</a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseSix" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-expanded="false" style="">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                <p>
                                  <strong>1. Purpose</strong> The Probation Policy of Technified Labs outlines the guidelines and procedures for employees who are placed on probationary status. This policy is designed to provide clear expectations, support, and opportunities for improvement to employees who may be struggling to meet performance standards or behavioral expectations.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>2. Scope</strong> This policy applies to all regular full-time and part-time employees of Technified Labs.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>3. Probationary Period</strong> 3.1. New Employees: Newly hired employees will typically undergo an initial probationary period, usually lasting [duration, e.g., 90 days], during which their performance, conduct, and overall fit within the company will be assessed.
                                </p>
                                <p>3.2. Existing Employees: In certain situations, existing employees may be placed on probation due to performance or conduct-related issues. The length of the probationary period for existing employees will be determined on a case-by-case basis.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>4. Expectations and Evaluation</strong> 4.1. Performance Goals: During the probationary period, employees will be provided with clear performance goals and expectations. These goals will be aligned with their job responsibilities and the company's performance standards.
                                </p>
                                <p>4.2. Evaluation: Regular performance evaluations will be conducted by the employee's supervisor or manager. These evaluations will include constructive feedback on the employee's progress, strengths, areas for improvement, and overall performance.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>5. Support and Improvement Plan</strong> 5.1. Support: Employees on probation will be provided with necessary resources, training, and support to help them meet performance expectations.
                                </p>
                                <p>5.2. Improvement Plan: In cases where an employee is struggling to meet expectations, a performance improvement plan (PIP) may be implemented. The PIP will outline specific areas for improvement, action steps, and a timeline for progress.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>6. Extension or Termination</strong> 6.1. Extension of Probation: In some cases, the probationary period may be extended to allow the employee additional time to demonstrate improvement. The decision to extend probation will be made by the employee's supervisor or manager, in consultation with HR.
                                </p>
                                <p>6.2. Termination: If an employee's performance, conduct, or overall fit within the company does not improve to the expected standards by the end of the probationary period or any extended period, termination of employment may result, in accordance with the company's progressive discipline process.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>7. Communication</strong> 7.1. Open Dialogue: Throughout the probationary period, there will be open and honest communication between the employee and their supervisor or manager. This will include regular feedback, performance discussions, and opportunities for the employee to voice their concerns or seek clarification.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>8. Confidentiality</strong> All discussions, evaluations, and decisions related to an employee's probationary status will be kept confidential among the involved parties, including the employee, their supervisor, and HR.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>9. Policy Review</strong> This Probation Policy will be reviewed periodically to ensure its effectiveness and relevance. Any necessary updates will be communicated to all employees.
                                </p>
                                <p>By providing a structured approach to probationary periods, Technified Labs aims to support employee growth, development, and success within the company.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel panel-default mb-1">
                        <div class="panel-heading1">
                            <h4 class="panel-title1">
                                <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseSeven" aria-expanded="false">Resignation and Exit Policy</a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseSeven" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-expanded="false" style="">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                               <p>
                                  <strong>1. Purpose</strong> The Resignation and Exit Policy of Technified Labs outlines the procedures and guidelines for employees who are resigning from their positions and the company's process for managing their departure. This policy ensures a smooth and professional transition for both the departing employee and the company.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>2. Scope</strong> This policy applies to all employees, regardless of their position or department, who intend to resign from their employment with Technified Labs.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>3. Resignation Process</strong> 3.1. Notice Period: Employees are required to provide [duration, e.g., two weeks] written notice of their intention to resign. The notice period allows the company to adequately plan for the transition and ensure a smooth handover of responsibilities.
                                </p>
                                <p>3.2. Written Resignation: Resignation notices should be submitted in writing to the employee's immediate supervisor or manager, as well as to the HR department. The resignation letter should include the intended last working day.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>4. Exit Interview</strong> 4.1. Purpose: An exit interview will be conducted with the resigning employee by a member of the HR department. The purpose of the exit interview is to gather feedback, insights, and suggestions from the departing employee about their experiences with the company.
                                </p>
                                <p>4.2. Confidentiality: The information shared during the exit interview will be kept confidential and used to improve the company's policies, practices, and work environment.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>5. Return of Company Property</strong> Departing employees are required to return all company property, including but not limited to laptops, access cards, security badges, keys, documents, and any other equipment provided by the company.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>6. Knowledge Transfer</strong> Employees who are leaving the company are expected to facilitate the smooth transfer of their knowledge, responsibilities, and ongoing projects to their colleagues, as determined by their supervisor or manager.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>7. Final Pay and Benefits</strong> 7.1. Final Paycheck: The employee's final paycheck, including any accrued but unused vacation days, will be processed according to the company's regular payroll schedule.
                                </p>
                                <p>7.2. Benefits: Employees will receive information about the continuation of benefits, such as health insurance, retirement plans, and any other applicable benefits, as per company policy and applicable laws.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>8. Confidentiality and Non-Disclosure</strong> Departing employees are expected to continue adhering to their confidentiality and non-disclosure obligations even after leaving the company. This includes safeguarding proprietary information, trade secrets, and client/customer information.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>9. Return of Confidential Information</strong> Employees are required to return or delete any company information, documents, files, or data they possess upon their departure, in order to protect sensitive and confidential information.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>10. Policy Review</strong> This Resignation and Exit Policy will be reviewed periodically to ensure its effectiveness and relevance. Any necessary updates will be communicated to all employees.
                                </p>
                                <p>By following the guidelines outlined in this policy, Technified Labs aims to ensure a professional and smooth transition for both resigning employees and the company.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel panel-default mb-1">
                        <div class="panel-heading1">
                            <h4 class="panel-title1">
                                <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseEight" aria-expanded="false">Joining Policy</a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
