                            <div class="panel-body">
                                <p>
                                  <strong>1. Purpose</strong> The Joining Policy of Technified Labs outlines the procedures and expectations for new employees joining the company. This policy ensures a seamless onboarding process that promotes understanding, integration, and productivity for both the new employee and the organization.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>2. Scope</strong> This policy applies to all new employees, including regular full-time and part-time employees, temporary workers, contractors, and interns, who are joining Technified Labs.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>3. Pre-Employment Process</strong> 3.1. Offer Acceptance: Upon receiving a formal offer of employment, candidates are expected to communicate their acceptance or decline in a timely manner.
                                </p>
                                <p>3.2. Required Documentation: New employees are required to submit all necessary documentation, such as identification, work authorization forms, and any other relevant paperwork, as requested by the HR department.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>4. Orientation and Onboarding</strong> 4.1. Welcome Orientation: New employees will attend a welcome orientation session on their first day. This session will provide an introduction to the company's mission, values, culture, policies, and key personnel.
                                </p>
                                <p>4.2. Onboarding Plan: Each new employee will receive an onboarding plan that outlines their initial training, departmental introductions, and expectations for the first few weeks.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>5. Employment Details</strong> 5.1. Employment Agreement: New employees will receive an employment agreement that outlines their terms of employment, including compensation, benefits, work hours, and other relevant details.
                                </p>
                                <p>5.2. Probation Period: New employees may undergo an initial probationary period as specified in the company's Probation Policy. During this period, performance and fit within the organization will be assessed.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>6. Training and Development</strong> New employees will receive job-specific training to ensure they have the necessary skills and knowledge to perform their roles effectively.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>7. IT and Security Access</strong> 7.1. IT Setup: The IT department will provide new employees with the necessary hardware, software, and access credentials to perform their job responsibilities.
                                </p>
                                <p>7.2. Security Awareness: New employees will receive information about the company's IT security policies and best practices to ensure the protection of company data.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>8. Benefits Enrollment</strong> New employees will receive information about the company's benefits package, including health insurance, retirement plans, and any other applicable benefits. They will also be provided with the necessary forms to enroll in these benefits.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>9. Performance Expectations</strong> 9.1. Job Description: New employees will receive a clear job description outlining their roles and responsibilities.
                                </p>
                                <p>9.2. Performance Goals: New employees will work with their managers to establish performance goals that align with the company's objectives.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>10. Policy Review</strong> This Joining Policy will be reviewed periodically to ensure its effectiveness and relevance. Any necessary updates will be communicated to all employees.
                                </p>
                                <p>By adhering to the guidelines outlined in this policy, Technified Labs aims to provide a positive and productive onboarding experience for all new employees.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="panel panel-default mb-1">
                        <div class="panel-heading1">
                            <h4 class="panel-title1">
                                <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseNine" aria-expanded="false">Recruitment Selection Policy</a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseNine" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-expanded="false" style="">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                <p>
                                  <strong>1. Purpose</strong> The Recruitment and Selection Policy of Technified Labs outlines the procedures, guidelines, and principles that govern the recruitment and selection process within the organization. This policy ensures fair, transparent, and consistent practices that align with the company's values and objectives.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>2. Scope</strong> This policy applies to all stages of the recruitment and selection process for all positions within Technified Labs, including regular full-time and part-time employees, temporary workers, contractors, and interns.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>3. Equal Opportunity</strong> Technified Labs is committed to providing equal employment opportunities to all individuals regardless of their race, color, religion, gender, sexual orientation, national origin, disability, or any other protected characteristic. The company seeks to create a diverse and inclusive workforce.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>4. Job Posting and Advertisement</strong> 4.1. Job Descriptions: All job postings will include clear and accurate job descriptions that outline the roles, responsibilities, and qualifications required for the position.
                                </p>
                                <p>4.2. Posting Locations: Job postings will be made available on the company's website, internal communication channels, and external job boards, as appropriate.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>5. Selection Criteria</strong> 5.1. Qualifications: Selection criteria will be based on the requirements of the job and will be consistently applied to all candidates.
                                </p>
                                <p>5.2. Objective Assessments: Assessment methods will be objective, job-related, and free from bias. These may include interviews, skill tests, assessment centers, and reference checks.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>6. Interview Process</strong> 6.1. Interview Panels: Interview panels will be composed of individuals who have received training on fair and unbiased interviewing practices.
                                </p>
                                <p>6.2. Consistency: Questions asked during interviews will be consistent across candidates and will focus on the candidates' qualifications, skills, and suitability for the role.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>7. Selection Decision</strong> 7.1. Selection Criteria: The selection decision will be based on the candidates' qualifications, skills, experience, and fit with the company culture.
                                </p>
                                <p>7.2. Offer of Employment: An offer of employment will be extended to the selected candidate, subject to the satisfactory completion of background checks and any other required assessments.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>8. Confidentiality</strong> All information collected during the recruitment and selection process will be treated confidentially and used solely for the purpose of evaluating candidates for employment.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>9. Candidate Feedback</strong> Candidates who are not selected for a position will be provided with respectful and constructive feedback upon request, subject to available resources.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>10. Policy Review</strong> This Recruitment and Selection Policy will be reviewed periodically to ensure its effectiveness and relevance. Any necessary updates will be communicated to all employees and stakeholders involved in the recruitment process.
                                </p>
                                <p>By adhering to the guidelines outlined in this policy, Technified Labs aims to attract, select, and hire qualified candidates who align with the company's values and contribute to its success.</p>
