                    <div class="panel panel-default mb-1">
                        <div class="panel-heading1">
                            <h4 class="panel-title1">
                                <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseEleven" aria-expanded="false">Leave Policy</a>
                            </h4>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseEleven" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-expanded="false" style="">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                               <p>
                                  <strong>1. Purpose</strong> The Leave Policy of Technified Labs outlines the guidelines and procedures for various types of leave available to employees. This policy ensures consistent and fair treatment of employees when it comes to taking time off from work for various reasons.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>2. Scope</strong> This policy applies to all employees of Technified Labs, including regular full-time and part-time employees, contractors, and temporary workers.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>3. Types of Leave</strong> Technified Labs provides the following types of leave to its employees:
                                </p>
                                <p>3.1. <strong>Paid Time Off (PTO)</strong>: PTO combines vacation, sick leave, and personal days into a single bank of time off that employees can use for any purpose. The amount of PTO granted will be based on the employee's tenure and job position. </p>
                                <p>3.2. <strong>Sick Leave</strong>: Sick leave is granted for employees to recover from illness or injury. Employees must provide appropriate documentation if the sick leave exceeds [duration, e.g., three consecutive days]. </p>
                                <p>3.3. <strong>Vacation Leave</strong>: Vacation leave allows employees to take time off for leisure, rest, and relaxation. The scheduling of vacation leave should be coordinated with the employee's supervisor and department to ensure smooth operations. </p>
                                <p>3.4. <strong>Public Holidays</strong>: Employees are entitled to observe designated public holidays as per company policy and local regulations. </p>
                                <p>3.5. <strong>Maternity and Paternity Leave</strong>: Technified Labs provides maternity and paternity leave in accordance with applicable laws. Employees can refer to the maternity and paternity leave policy for specific details. </p>
                                <p>3.6. <strong>Bereavement Leave</strong>: A certain number of days of paid leave may be granted to employees in case of the death of an immediate family member. </p>
                                <p>3.7. <strong>Special Leave</strong>: Special leave may be granted in exceptional circumstances, such as family emergencies or personal situations, on a case-by-case basis. </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>4. Leave Request Procedure</strong> 4.1. Advance Notice: Employees are required to submit leave requests in advance, except in cases of emergency. The notice period for different types of leave may vary, and employees should follow the company's designated procedure.
                                </p>
                                <p>4.2. Approval Process: Leave requests will be reviewed and approved by the employee's supervisor or manager. The company reserves the right to deny leave requests if operational requirements cannot be met.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>5. Documentation</strong> Appropriate documentation, such as medical certificates, may be required for certain types of leave, especially for extended absences or sick leave.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>6. Return to Work</strong> Employees returning from leave are expected to report to work on the specified date and resume their duties promptly.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>7. Leave Carryover and Encashment</strong> The company's policy on carrying over unused leave from one year to the next and the encashment of leave will be communicated separately.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>8. Policy Review</strong> This Leave Policy will be reviewed periodically to ensure its effectiveness and relevance. Any necessary updates will be communicated to all employees.
                                </p>
                                <p>By adhering to the guidelines outlined in this policy, Technified Labs aims to support employees in maintaining a healthy work-life balance while ensuring the smooth functioning of the organization.</p>
