                        <div id="collapseFourteen" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-expanded="false" style="">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                                <p>
                                  <strong>1. Purpose</strong> The Confidentiality Policy of Technified Labs outlines the guidelines and expectations for handling confidential and proprietary information. This policy is designed to protect sensitive company information, trade secrets, client data, and other confidential materials from unauthorized access, disclosure, or use.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>2. Scope</strong> This policy applies to all employees, contractors, consultants, interns, and any other individuals who have access to confidential information through their association with Technified Labs.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>3. Definition of Confidential Information</strong> Confidential information includes, but is not limited to, proprietary software, financial data, business plans, client lists, research and development projects, marketing strategies, employee data, and any information that is not publicly available.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>4. Obligations</strong> 4.1. Protection: All individuals covered by this policy have an obligation to protect confidential information from unauthorized access, disclosure, or use.
                                </p>
                                <p>4.2. Non-Disclosure Agreements: Employees who have access to confidential information may be required to sign non-disclosure agreements (NDAs) to formalize their commitment to confidentiality.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>5. Handling Confidential Information</strong> 5.1. Access Limitation: Confidential information should only be accessed by employees with a legitimate need for such access.
                                </p>
                                <p>5.2. Secure Storage: Confidential information must be stored securely, both physically and digitally, and protected with appropriate security measures, such as encryption and access controls.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>6. Sharing and Disclosure</strong> 6.1. Authorized Sharing: Confidential information may only be shared with individuals within the company who have a legitimate need to know and who are bound by similar confidentiality obligations.
                                </p>
                                <p>6.2. External Disclosure: Disclosure of confidential information to external parties, such as vendors, clients, or partners, must be authorized by management and accompanied by a confidentiality agreement if necessary.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>7. Data Privacy and Compliance</strong> Confidential information that includes personal data of employees, clients, or others must be handled in compliance with relevant data protection laws and regulations.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>8. Handling After Employment</strong> Employees must continue to adhere to confidentiality obligations even after their employment with Technified Labs ends. This includes returning or destroying confidential materials in their possession.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>9. Policy Violations</strong> Violations of this policy, including unauthorized access, disclosure, or use of confidential information, may result in disciplinary actions, up to and including termination of employment.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>10. Reporting Concerns</strong> Any concerns or suspicions of a breach of confidentiality should be reported to the appropriate supervisor, manager, or the HR department.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>11. Policy Review</strong> This Confidentiality Policy will be reviewed periodically to ensure its effectiveness and relevance. Any necessary updates will be communicated to all employees.
                                </p>
                                <p>By adhering to the guidelines outlined in this policy, Technified Labs aims to safeguard its confidential information and maintain the trust of clients, partners, and stakeholders.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
