                            <div class="panel-body">
                               <p>
                                  <strong>1. Purpose</strong> The Assets Policy of Technified Labs outlines the guidelines for the proper use, management, and protection of company assets. This policy is designed to ensure that company resources are used efficiently, maintained appropriately, and safeguarded against loss, theft, or misuse.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>2. Scope</strong> This policy applies to all employees, contractors, interns, and any other individuals who have access to company assets through their association with Technified Labs.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>3. Definition of Assets</strong> Company assets include, but are not limited to, physical equipment, electronic devices, software, vehicles, intellectual property, facilities, furniture, supplies, and any other items owned or leased by Technified Labs.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>4. Asset Responsibility</strong> 4.1. Custodianship: Designated employees are responsible for the care, maintenance, and proper use of specific assets assigned to them.
                                </p>
                                <p>4.2. Reporting Changes: Any changes in asset location, condition, or status should be promptly reported to the appropriate department or supervisor.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>5. Proper Use and Maintenance</strong> 5.1. Authorized Use: Assets should only be used for legitimate business purposes in accordance with company policies and guidelines.
                                </p>
                                <p>5.2. Maintenance: Employees should ensure that assets are used and maintained in a manner that preserves their functionality, appearance, and value.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>6. Protection and Security</strong> 6.1. Security Measures: Assets should be secured to prevent theft, loss, or damage. This may include using locking mechanisms, access controls, and appropriate storage.
                                </p>
                                <p>6.2. Confidential Information: Assets that store confidential or sensitive information must be protected with additional security measures to prevent unauthorized access.</p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>7. Return and Retrieval</strong> Employees leaving the company or transferring departments are responsible for returning all assigned assets. The receiving party should ensure that the asset is in proper condition and accurately documented.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>8. Software and Intellectual Property</strong> Employees must adhere to software licensing agreements and intellectual property rights when using company software, tools, and proprietary information.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>9. Disposal and Retirement</strong> Assets that are no longer needed or functional should be disposed of in accordance with the company's asset disposal procedure, which may involve recycling, donating, or proper disposal methods.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>10. Reporting Loss or Damage</strong> Employees are required to report any loss, theft, damage, or malfunction of company assets to their supervisor or the appropriate department immediately.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>11. Policy Violations</strong> Misuse, unauthorized transfer, theft, or damage of company assets may result in disciplinary actions, up to and including termination of employment.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                  <strong>12. Policy Review</strong> This Assets Policy will be reviewed periodically to ensure its effectiveness and relevance. Any necessary updates will be communicated to all employees.
                                </p>
                                <p>By adhering to the guidelines outlined in this policy, Technified Labs aims to ensure the responsible use, management, and protection of its valuable assets.</p>
